"n.危险 【英】 n. 危险( exposure to the risk ; danger) n. 极大的危险 = danger 【记】per全部, il = ill: 全部器官要得病－危险 【参】perilous(adj 危险的) = hazardous 【记】音：破肉，肉破了流血了就危险了；per- through + ill 病透了→危险 peril (n.)  c.1200, from Old French peril ""danger, risk"" (10c.), from Latin periculum ""an attempt, trial, experiment; risk, danger,"" with instrumentive suffix -culum and element also found in experiri ""to try,"" cognate with Greek peria ""trial, attempt, experience,"" empeiros ""experienced,"" Old Irish aire ""vigilance,"" Gothic ferja ""watcher,"" Old English fær ""danger, fear"" (see fear (n.))."
